Action Arguments Returns <code>execute</code> <code>{"sql", "params", "max_rows", "timeout"}</code> <code>{columns, rows, row_count, truncated}</code> <code>explain</code> <code>{"sql", "params"}</code> the dialect's query plan <pre><code>{
  "action": "execute",
  "params_json": "{\"sql\": \"SELECT id, name FROM users WHERE id = :id\", \"params\": {\"id\": 1}, \"max_rows\": 100}",
  "connection": "warehouse"
}
</code></pre> <p>Statements must be single and read-only (<code>SELECT</code>/<code>WITH</code>/<code>EXPLAIN</code>/<code>SHOW</code>/ <code>DESCRIBE</code>/<code>PRAGMA</code>/<code>VALUES</code>); values bind via <code>:name</code> parameters. <code>max_rows</code> is clamped to the server's <code>SQL_MAX_ROWS</code>. EXPLAIN is unavailable on MSSQL (it has no statement-level EXPLAIN).</p>
